    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The application is designed with a user-friendly tabbed navigation structure (學習成長, 生活發展, 親師合作, 老師的話). This thematic approach allows parents to directly access the information they need most, rather than following the linear structure of the original outline. This non-linear exploration enhances usability and engagement. Each tab reveals a section with interactive cards, making the text-heavy content more digestible and visually appealing. The goal is to create an intuitive, self-guided resource for parents. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: Since the source material is entirely qualitative, no data charts are needed. The focus is on organizing and presenting text effectively. Goal: Inform & Organize. Presentation Method: Interactive cards and styled text blocks created with HTML/Tailwind CSS. Interaction: Users click on navigation tabs to switch between content sections, providing a clean and focused view. This avoids overwhelming the user with all information at once. Justification: This design choice turns a static document into a dynamic and engaging guide, which is more suitable for a web application and a modern audience. Library/Method: Vanilla JavaScript for tab functionality. -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
